ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v24.group

Class ORF_R04_RESPONSE

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractStructure
      • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractGroup
        • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v24.group.ORF_R04_RESPONSE
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Group, Structure, Visitable, Serializable

    public class ORF_R04_RESPONSE
extends AbstractGroup

    Represents a ORF_R04_RESPONSE group structure (a Group object). A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in/excluded together. This Group contains the following elements:

    • 1: ORF_R04_PATIENT (a Group object) optional
    • 2: ORF_R04_ORDER (a Group object) repeating

        public List<ORF_R04_ORDER> getORDERAll()
                                throws HL7Exception

        Returns a non-modifiable List containing all current existing repetitions of ORDER.

        Note that unlike getORDER(), this method will not create any reps if none are already present, so an empty list may be returned.
